      <hedline>
        <hl1>My Name Is Not Robert</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Dr Andrew Angel letter on Benjamin Weiser's August 6 article on wrongful imprisonment of Kerry Sanders holds there is recurring pattern in which criminal justice system seems more motivated to make any conviction (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>I see a recurring pattern in which the criminal justice system is seemingly more motivated to make any conviction rather than the correct one. From judges to district attorneys to prison psychiatrists, there is a disturbing resistance by those in charge to review and reconsider the facts of a case whose circumstances are less than clear.</p>
        <p>Andrew Angel, M.D.  Cambridge, Mass.</p>
      </block>
